.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-2-5::.
The people grow 7 different varities of flowers: iris, daisy, daffodil, amaryllis, lily, begonia, dahlia
The people use 7 different means of transport: bike, helicopter, motorbike, ship, skateboard, train, van
1. the person driving the ship is on the right of the person driving the skateboard##1
2. the person driving the skateboard is the person who growsdaisy##1
3. the person driving the bike is between the person who growsdahlia and the person who growsiris##2
4. the person who growsbegonia is on the right of the person driving the skateboard##1
5. the person driving the bike is in the middle##1
6. the person driving the train is on the left of the person who growsiris##1
7. the person driving the motorbike is on the left of the person driving the skateboard##1
8. the person driving the helicopter is the person who growsamaryllis##1
9. the person who growslily is the person driving the train##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |   2   |     3     |  4   |     5     |     6      |  7   |
| Flower   | amaryllis      | lily | iris | daffodil | dahlia      | daisy      | begonia |
| Transport     | helicopter | train | van       | bike | motorbike | skateboard | ship |

